{"questionId":"11930","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Saloni wants to find a model for the temperature of a bottle of water after she removes it from the fridge. She uses a temperature probe to record the temperature of the water, every 5 minutes.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/e0e3e0c85b8be5fd992a7706300644908ac9f9b7.png\"></p>\n<p>After graphing the data, Saloni believes a suitable model will be</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T = 28 - a{b^t}\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>28</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b \\in {\\mathbb{R}^ + }\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Interpret what the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{R^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;tells you about the model.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Since the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{R^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is close to +1, the model is a good fit for the data.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp;R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11930","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.21c.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Interpret what the value of R 2 tells you about the model.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}